summary: An ordinance accepting a deed from Edward B. Ballinger and Julia L. Ballinger, his wife, and B. V. Williams and Edith L. Williams, his wife, and Roy J. Henderson, a bachelor, dated the 18th day of July, 1916, creating a right of way and easement over and across certain portions of lots 10, 11, and 12, of a replat of block 54, Burke's 2nd Addition to the City of Seattle, King County, State of Washington, and declaring an emergency.
